      <h1 class="page-title" id="overview">Overview</h1>
      <div class="page-meta">
        <span>The AURA Lab</span><span class="dot">&middot;</span>
        <span>William &amp; Mary, Department of Computer Science</span><span class="dot">&middot;</span>
        <span>Founded Fall 2024</span>
      </div>

      <p class="lead">
        The AURA Lab advances research at the intersection of efficiency, automation, and
        explainability in software engineering. Our mission is to design innovative and
        responsible AI-driven solutions that improve developer productivity while
        addressing key challenges of transparency and resource efficiency. Through
        rigorous methods, open collaboration, and a commitment to impactful work, the
        AURA Lab contributes practical advances in AI-supported software engineering
        for academia, industry, and society.
      </p>

      <div class="callout">
        <span class="tag">Acronym</span>
        <p><strong>AURA</strong> &mdash; <strong>A</strong>I for <strong>U</strong>nderstandable
        and <strong>R</strong>esponsible <strong>A</strong>utomation in Software Engineering.
        Directed by Dr. Antonio Mastropaolo, Assistant Professor at William &amp; Mary.</p>
      </div>

